[The risk of contracting rabies by people who have been bitten or
scratched, or had mucous membranes or broken skin licked by any dog
in the risk areas during the relevant periods is low but finite.
Travelers to the areas specified should avoid contact with domestic
and stray cats and dogs and other susceptible animals until the alert
has been cancelled. It will be interesting to see how this incident
affects the rabies-free status of France.

The interactive HealthMap of France is available at
<http://healthmap.org/promed?v=46.6,2.6,5>. - Mod.CP]
